{
  "texts": [
    "We let Σ ψ be the extended surface obtained from Σ by identifying N and M under the map ψ.",
    "The resulting decorated surface Σ ψ depends only on the isotopy class of ψ ([40, Lemma 4.1.1]).Let the identification ψ be fixed and write Σ gl for the glued surface.",
    "Given a string diagram x on Σ we say the boundary conditions x M and x N match if all corresponding pairs of marked boundary points (m, ψ(m)) ∈ m N × m M are labelled by the same object.",
    "Suppose this is the case for x.",
    "Let us write x gl for the string diagram obtained by interpreting x as a string diagram on Σ gl: gl -→.Setting [x gl] = 0 if the boundary conditions do not match, the gluing of string diagrams descends to a well-defined gluing map gl: A(Σ) → A(Σ gl) by setting gl([x]):= [x gl] and extending to A(Σ) by linearity."
  ]
}